    "summary": "\" I am an international expert on counter-terrorism and countering violent extremism with a sincere dedication for connecting and inspiring people, nations and international organisations. I am convinced that it is necessary to bring research, expertise and practical experiences together, in order to make a sustainable change and effective contribution to human security and international justice. I am currently looking for new job opportunities.\"\nVan Ginkel is a Research Fellow at the ICCT and a senior research fellow at the Security Unit of the Research Department of the Clingendael for International Relations. Van Ginkel has helped build ICCT from the start and attain its current international reputation.\nVan Ginkel\u2019s expertise spans the wide variety of focus areas of ICCT, from rule of law issues to trends and threat developments, counter-terrorism, countering violent extremism responses, and prevention strategies. She has vast experience in leading and coordinating highly complicated, multi-stakeholder and international (research) projects. Furthermore, her experience extends to the role of consultant and implementing partner for international organisations, of trainer and moderator, and of specialist in monitoring and evaluation of policies.  She has established close working relationships with the UN, the EU and other international organisations, as well as with government agencies and civil society actors. She is also often invited as a (keynote) speaker to international conferences. She has briefed the Dutch Parliament, Standing Committee on Defence several times on topical security questions, the Green Party at the German Parliament, and the Flemish Parliament on issues of Radicalisation, as well as UNCTED, the LIBE Committee of the European Parliament, the joint COTER/TWP meeting of the European Union, CODEXTER (Council of Europe), and the UN Special Rapporteur on Contemporary Forms of Racism, Racial Discrimination, and Xenophobia.",
